Ingredients

- 1 cup of garri
- 6 cubes of sugar
- 1 sachet of Nido
- 1 packet of fried groundnut.
- 1 bottle of tangui water

Procedure

- Pray the lords prayer
- pour your garri into a sizeable bowl
- add water quick while stirring. This is to sort of wash the garri, which is usually not so clean. Then drain the water added quickly which should have some particles suspended in it.
- Find your self a good spoon and just a friend to share a meal. 
